-- Egyptian Stocks: Beltone Financial, Orascom Telecom Media
-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 2012-02-02T13:33:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-02/egyptian-stocks-beltone-financial-orascom-telecom-media.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index 
declined 2.2 percent, the most since Dec. 22, to 4,584.39 at the
2:30 p.m. close in Cairo, trimming this week’s gain to 3.4
percent.  The following were among active stocks on the Egyptian
Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Beltone Financial Holding (BTFH)   dropped 9.2 percent to
12.42 Egyptian pounds, the lowest since Dec. 26. Chief Executive
Officer Aladdin Saba canceled the sale of his 20 percent stake
in the investment bank to  Arabia Investments & Development &
Financial Investments Holding Co .  Orascom Telecom Media & Technology Holding SAE  (OTMT EY)
advanced for an eighth day, gaining 1.8 percent to 1.14 pounds.
The mobile-phone company headed by billionaire Naguib Sawiris
said its subscribers in  North Korea  exceeded one million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
